<subSubSection id="3C117FF0996A727E9A992263E17FE0EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="description">
<paragraph id="C169A66744B5A6C9C172E0479B6D95AE" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A796B2539B49675389BC94ED79518C77" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="3DF7837867028C659A117146DF451849" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male. Coloration</emphasis>
: Body chestnut brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="59B8FD8828D52F08E671946B24C82CB6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4A, B</figureCitation>
). Vertex black, lower half of face chestnut brown. Ocelli milky. Base of antenna yellowish brown, the rest dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EACA318D491189F7A403BDDE9343ADEB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4C</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palps brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="67377C84CE8D37117AA61FC3EC80D6E8" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4E</figureCitation>
). Pronotum chestnut brown, posterior and narrow lateral borders shiny black (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BE082CD891A87F4F3F340BF7B08F8A28" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4D</figureCitation>
). Tegmina anterior edge black, the rest blackish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B04404ADEF1771834281FF031DAE02FB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4H</figureCitation>
). Legs with tibiae and tarsi dark brown, remainder chestnut brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="03B2FB2DB5CFFA67EA821C40D0360851" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="005FF3526A8E46B3DC2986CCFB9B73C3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Head</emphasis>
: Interocular space shorter than the distance between ocelli and slightly less than the width of an antennal socket. Third maxillary palpomere as long as the fourth, slightly longer than the fifth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0F2CBAD302DC4E4275D0230E71079A03" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4E</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of pronotum slightly convex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1CC4882AE87B858BBB6134EE0B1CE41B" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="99D65AE96DA358EA1E6DFF04A1DFB313" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Tegmina and hindwings</emphasis>
: Both fully developed, extending beyond the end of abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8E6E15CED984437CBDFDFF565CEE79E6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4H, I</figureCitation>
). Hind wings with RP branched after the midpoint, the apical region of M with a bifurcation, CuA slightly curved with 5 complete and 3 incomplete branches (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3BBBE641DBE30996D2CDA67E1563D3E8" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4I</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="34B3913F85D5DD0FFE246E397C183FFA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Legs</emphasis>
: Front femur Type A3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AB5289CBDCE5F7EE1A9B04C2E4371333" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4F</figureCitation>
), pretarsal claws symmetrical and unspecialized, pulvillus present. 
<emphasis id="ED6C4970BD328825FF6ADA83E53427E5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Abdominal tergites</emphasis>
: T1 specialized as a ridge scattered with a cluster of setae. T7 also specialized with a pair of unobvious fossae in the middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B1523F78064B9D7C601CBFEE82A8C80B" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4G</figureCitation>
). T10 symmetrical, posterior margin rounded. 
<emphasis id="DFB7CFCDFDCB28D093BC698F2BB154A2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Paraprocts</emphasis>
: Dissimilar, the right one bifurcate with one apex enlarged, left one with a curved finger-like process (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FD9F46B16A19023A97E0A0B0AEC0356F" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4J</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="36485ACF26B459D915209F1A3206AF2A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Subgenital plate</emphasis>
: Slightly asymmetrical, middle part of posterior margin distinctly convex with tiny bristles, two styli similar and cylindrical with tiny bristles; right middle area with a large spine-like protrusion pointed to supra-anal plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4A46D340DAF1ED4583D594C35BDC5828" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4N</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="56552B8B0B21D9E4D14B9E8619E105E7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: L3 on the left side and the apex with an incision (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="79909BC8F37BEAB50EA0852AE0AB3819" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4K</figureCitation>
); L2vm rod-like, the apex acute (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E00FBF507B47CE3BC40B7456D13F3817" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4L</figureCitation>
); R3 complex, a part of the sclerites rake-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9C2530C21610B79D7C507937ECAA5DE3" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Symploce nigra sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690404" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">4M</figureCitation>
). - 
<emphasis id="05B2D63A97FF8C3AFD8100F6617F2E05" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
